===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[ladies]] and [[gentlemen]]|[[plurale tantum]]}}

# {{idiom}} Used to address an [[audience]].

====Usage notes====
* Use is so idiomatic that unisex audiences are also often addressed with this term, though "ladies" or "gentlemen" would be more correct.
* The forms "lady and gentlemen" and "ladies and gentleman" are rarely used even when strictly correct.

